race.comment: A lot of these have the ability but struggling to break through. CABLE DE VEGA (5) at least has recent winning form having won two of last five. Tackled the Great Western Cup last time and wasn't far away in fourth. Back in grade and on recent form looks hard to beat. ALL TORQUE (3) is fitter for three runs back and looks ready to find an overdue win. Has been stretched to this sort of journey a couple of times and nothing has really gone right. Runner-up last time over a mile and over the longer trip expected to feature if on song. VELLASGLORY (2) is racing well and looks serious threat.  Winner two back here then tried to lead throughout at Seymour and run over late. Worth another chance. OUTCASTER (10) is better than recent form and off the inside gets chance. FRANK EXPRESS (1) drew wide last time and and went forward but sat three deep the trip and faded right out of it. Drawn a fraction better and has the claim and with an easier run can give a sight.
